results.name: Decimal expansion of the 5th Du Bois Reymond constant.
comment: The k-th Du Bois Reymond constant c_k is asymptotic to 2/(1+r^2)^(k/2), where r = A115365 = 4.4934094579090641753... is smallest positive root of the equation tan(r) = r. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Aug 20 2014
reference: S. R. Finch, Mathematical Constants, Cambridge, 2003, pp. 237-239.
link: Vaclav Kotesovec, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..450
Eric Weisstein's MathWorld, Du Bois Reymond Constants.
